zoomBox(25.10)                                                  zoomBox(25.10)

Name
       zoomBox  -  Zooms  in the viewable window to the area that encloses the
       specified coordinates

Syntax
       zoomBox

       [-help]

       <area>

       Zooms in the viewable window to the area that  encloses  the  specified
       coordinates.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each zoomBox parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man zoomBox.

       <area> Specifies the coordinates for the box representing the area into
              which you want to zoom.

Example
       The following command zooms in the viewable window to the area enclosed
       by the lower-left coordinates (450 531) and the upper-right coordinates
       (550 631)

       zoomBox 450 531 550 631

